er writing tests for the new functional feature involving the @Timed annotation. My concern is about the extraTags array in the assertion and how class-level annotations interact with method annotations. It might be beneficial to name the test something like `timedAnnotationsPreferRepositoryMethodAnnotationsAndFallBackToTypeAnnotations` to cover method precedence and fallback in one go, without duplicates. I also need to ensure I've imported the right classes and handle the assertions correctly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_BbKXs7TMl8NpJ6LVDhqhNePe|fc_0f31f5ceec0fa013016a0cdb6000348197a21248f1f50b5a94", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-data-commons/4.0.6/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot_data_commons/Spring_boot_data_commonsTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Collections;", "newText": "import java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Collections;"}, {"oldText": "import io.micrometer.core.instrument.Tag;", "newText": "import io.micrometer.core.annotation.Timed;\nimport io.micrometer.core.instrument.Tag;"}, {"oldText": "import org.springframework.boot.data.metrics.MetricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListener;", "newText": "import org.springframework.boot.data.metrics.MetricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListener;\nimport org.springframework.boot.data.metrics.TimedAnnotations;"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void metricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListenerRecordsSuccessfulInvocations() {\n        String metricName = \"test.repository.invocations\";\n        long duration = TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.toNanos(25);\n        SimpleMeterRegistry registry = new SimpleMeterRegistry();\n        MetricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListener listener = new MetricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListener(\n                () -> registry, new DefaultRepositoryTagsProvider(), metricName, AutoTimer.ENABLED);\n\n        listener.afterInvocation(repositoryInvocation(State.SUCCESS, null, duration));\n\n        Timer timer = registry.get(metricName)\n            .tags(\"repository\", \"SampleRepository\", \"state\", \"SUCCESS\", \"exception\", \"None\")\n            .timer();\n        assertThat(timer.count()).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(timer.totalTime(TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS)).isEqualTo(25.0);\n    }\n\n    private static <T> T bind(String prefix, Class<T> type, Map<String, String> values) {", "newText": "    @Test\n    void metricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListenerRecordsSuccessfulInvocations() {\n        String metricName = \"test.repository.invocations\";\n        long duration = TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.toNanos(25);\n        SimpleMeterRegistry registry = new SimpleMeterRegistry();\n        MetricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListener listener = new MetricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListener(\n                () -> registry, new DefaultRepositoryTagsProvider(), metricName, AutoTimer.ENABLED);\n\n        listener.afterInvocation(repositoryInvocation(State.SUCCESS, null, duration));\n\n        Timer timer = registry.get(metricName)\n            .tags(\"repository\", \"SampleRepository\", \"state\", \"SUCCESS\", \"exception\", \"None\")\n            .timer();\n        assertThat(timer.count()).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(timer.totalTime(TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS)).isEqualTo(25.0);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void timedAnnotationsPreferRepositoryMethodAnnotationsAndFallBackToTypeAnnotations() throws NoSuchMethodException {\n        Method annotatedMethod = TimedRepository.class.getMethod(\"findOneByName\", String.class);\n        Method unannotatedMethod = TimedRepository.class.getMethod(\"countByName\", String.class);\n\n        assertThat(TimedAnnotations.get(annotatedMethod, TimedRepository.class)).singleElement()\n            .satisfies((annotation) -> assertTimedAnnotation(annotation, \"method.repository.invocations\", \"method\",\n                    \"findOneByName\"));\n        assertThat(TimedAnnotations.get(unannotatedMethod, TimedRepository.class)).singleElement()\n            .satisfies((annotation) -> assertTimedAnnotation(annotation, \"type.repository.invocations\", \"level\",\n                    \"repository\"));\n    }\n\n    private static <T> T bind(String prefix, Class<T> type, Map<String, String> values) {"}, {"oldText": "    private interface SampleRepository extends Repository<SampleEntity, Long> {\n\n    }\n\n    private static final class SampleEntity {", "newText": "    private static void assertTimedAnnotation(Timed annotation, String metricName, String... extraTags) {\n        assertThat(annotation.value()).isEqualTo(metricName);\n        assertThat(annotation.extraTags()).containsExactly(extraTags);\n    }\n\n    private interface SampleRepository extends Repository<SampleEntity, Long> {\n\n    }\n\n    @Timed(value = \"type.repository.invocations\", extraTags = { \"level\", \"repository\" })\n    private interface TimedRepository extends Repository<SampleEntity, Long> {\n\n        @Timed(value = \"method.repository.invocations\", extraTags = { \"method\", \"findOneByName\" })\n        SampleEntity findOneByName(String name);\n\n        long countByName(String name);\n\n    }\n\n    private static final class SampleEntity {"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2559, "output": 2778, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27865, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779227462130, "responseId": "resp_0f31f5ceec0fa013016a0cdb4696c08197b445f7ec2a2dc21b"}}
